---

## Notes

- Baud rate is **9600**
- IR codes land on **DP2** in TuyaReceived but must be **sent on DP7** — different DPs for receive vs transmit
- The dedicated IR MCU handles all timing — Tasmota just passes the raw code blob through
- TuyaSend5/TuyaSend6 Tasmota commands do NOT work reliably for this device — use **SerialSend5** with manually built packets only
- Each button press during study captures one code — repeat for every button you want to control
